# 4. 旅は道連れ

Airi: Alright, let's head to the shrine for the performing arts!
Tsukasa & Shizuku: Yes!
Airi: Actually, before we do, mind if we take a quick detour?
Tsukasa & Shizuku: Huh?
Mafuyu: Where, Momoi?
Airi: Between here and the shrine, there's supposed to be a big street with lots of shops... We should be able to buy souvenirs and have a quick tea break.
Airi: So, would that be okay? It'll also give you two a chance to find some souvenirs like you said.
Rui: Yes, that sounds good.
Airi: Great! Then, we'll start with the street of souvenir shops!
Tsukasa & Shizuku: Okay!
Shizuku: Wow...! So many shops...!
Mafuyu: Let's see... Based on this map, there's a souvenir shop on the street just ahead, with a little tea shop further along.
Tsukasa: Oh, that bulletin says a new Japanese sweet shop apparently just opened up in the area where the tea shop is. It seems very popular.
Airi: Japanese sweets?! That's definitely going on the list...!
Airi: Shizuku, we gotta check it out later and–
Shizuku: Oh wow...! These candies look like gemstones!
Rui: Yes, these could work very well as a stage prop if we made a ring using some. I can see it already... The king eats his own ring as he goes mad with power...
Airi & Tsukasa: *Sigh* Oh dear...
Shizuku: Oh, you can try this mochi? Then, I'd like a sample!
Airi: Hey, don't wander off without us! Have you forgotten that your phone's out of battery?!
Rui: Oh, a textile shop. It'd be nice to make some costumes out of these fabrics someday.
Tsukasa: Hey, that goes for you too! Don't wander off like that!
Mafuyu: This is turning into quite a lively day...
Airi: Alright, let's find some souvenirs for our nearest and dearest!
Airi: Mutsuhashi are pretty standard... But I kinda want to get something more fun.
Shizuku: Oh, how about these? Grapefruit-flavored mutsuhashi gummies!
Tsukasa: Grapefruit-flavored mutsuhashi gummies?!
Mafuyu: That's quite the combination...
Airi: I guess this kind of tragedy is what happens when the tourism industry goes a little too far...
Rui: But they could be worth getting. Emu likes these sorts of strange snacks, and Nene likes grapefruit.
Tsukasa: That doesn't justify buying these!
Mafuyu: Ena might like some of these blotting sheets...
Airi: You're getting those for her, Asahina? Then, I think I'll get this powder puff...
Shizuku: Hehe. It would've been nice to also run into Ena here since we're all second years.
Airi: That's sorta doubtful since night school students don't have their trip at the same time as regular students.
Airi: So, we should take this opportunity to get her some nice gifts!
Tsukasa: Hmm... I'm not seeing one anywhere...
Mafuyu: What are you looking for, Tenma?
Tsukasa: Oh, one of those golden Kyoto figurines...
Airi: Golden Kyoto figurines...?
Rui: Do you mean one of those porcelain dolls made in Kyoto, but colored gold...?
Airi: Wait, what are you talking about?! There's no way they make those!
Tsukasa: That's unfortunate... I've searched for them everywhere to no avail... I was hoping to get one for Saki.
Shizuku: Oh, you're looking for something for Saki? In that case...
Shizuku: How about some of these colorful comfits? They look like little stars.
Tsukasa: Oh, you're right! And they're very cute! Excellent idea!
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm glad to hear that. I think I'll get some for Shii.
Shizuku: How adorable is it going to be when they have these together with their friends?
Tsukasa: Yes...! A harmonious scene indeed!
Airi: Oh... Thank goodness... Saki's going to get a real gift...
Tsukasa: Okay, that should do it for souvenirs...
Mafuyu: Oh, I see a Japanese sweet shop up ahead. Shall we take a break there?
Airi: Yeah! Hehe. I can't wait to see what they have♪ Huh?!
Airi: Wh-Where'd Shizuku go?!
Tsukasa: Wh-What?! This is terrible...!
Rui: It is...?
Tsukasa: Yes, because she's—
Shizuku's Voice: Oh, this is so lovely...!
Airi: *Gasp* There she is!
Old Store Clerk: I'm sure it'll look very good on you, miss.
Shizuku: Thank you very much! But this looks so well made... I'm not sure I can afford it...
Old Store Clerk: Hehe. You're in for a nice surprise. I make these as a part of my hobby. How does this much sound?
Shizuku: Oh, my allowance can cover that...! Then, if you don't mind...
Old Store Clerk: Yes, of course!
Airi: Shizuku! Again, your phone has no power, so losing sight of you immediately turns into a big emergency!
Shizuku: Oh! Hi, Airi...!
Rui: She's prone to getting lost?
Tsukasa: Yes... Her sense of direction leaves something to be desired...
Shizuku: I'm sorry. I found something wonderful that really caught my attention...
Tsukasa: Something wonderful?
Shizuku: Yes, this.
Rui: Ah, what a lovely haori.
Rui: These snowflakes... They've been embroidered so carefully onto this white fabric...
Shizuku: Hehe. That's also what I liked about it.
Airi: Yeah, it's really pretty... But when are you gonna wear it?
Shizuku: I was thinking of using it as a bed jacket since I'm not sure when I'd wear this outside.
Airi: R-Really?! A bed jacket?! This looks way too nice for that!
Shizuku: W-Would that be bad?
Airi: No, but... I guess that does suit you best.
Airi: Anyway, now that we're all back together, let's head over to that sweet shop!
Tsukasa: Right! And after that, we can head over to the shrine for the performing arts!
Tsukasa: Alright, we're here! And still all together...
Mafuyu: So, shall we go make our wishes?
Airi: Okay! Ready, everyone!
Tsukasa: I will!!! Become!!! The world's greatest star!!!
Airi: Whoa...! Who shouts like that while making their wish?!
Mafuyu: Th-That was alarming...
Rui: I agree... I'm used to this in your case, but I doubt many people shout out their wishes the way you did...
Tsukasa: W-Wait, but...! I need to be loud if I want this shrine's deity to hear me, no?!
Airi: Th-They probably felt your presence...
Shizuku: Hehe... Hehehe...
Mafuyu: Is something the matter, Hinomori?
Shizuku: Oh, I'm sorry... It's just... Tsukasa really hasn't changed since we were little.
Rui: Actually, Hinomori... How long have you two known each other?
Airi: Yeah, I didn't ask you that. It seems like you two have known each other forever...
Shizuku: I've known Tsukasa since we were in elementary school.
Mafuyu: So, you're childhood friends?
Tsukasa: Actually... We didn't play that often together, but I suppose we're something like that...
Shizuku: Yes, that seems fair.
Shizuku: I first met him when we were in second grade...
